collections::​sequential_collection
interface
collections::​ .​sequential_collection
collections::​ .​deque

A collection which supports efficient element access using integer indices via the get() method and defines a size() method that returns the length of the sequence.

methods
get
pure virtual function T get(
int 
index
)

Returns the item at the specified index.

Invalid indices are handled gracefully by returning a default value.

An implementation may also optionally issue a warning on an access attempt to an invalid index.

size
pure virtual function int size()

Returns the current size of the container.

Implementations shoud return an integer value greater or equal to 0, where 0 is returned for an empty container.

index
pure virtual function int index(
T 
item
)

Find the index of the first occurence of an item in the collection.

implementations should return a zero-based index of the first item whose value is equal to _item.

implementations should return -1 to indicate that _item could not be found and is not a part of the collection.

count
pure virtual function int count(
T 
item
)

Return the number of times item appears in the collection.

is_empty
pure virtual function bit is_empty()

Returns 1 if a collection is empty, or 0 otherwise.
